  "text": "Quantitative kinetic real-time PCRs (qPCRs) of narG [narG1960f (TAY GTS GGS CAR GAR AA)/narG2650r (TTY TCR TAC CAB GTB GC); [CITATION_1] , nosZ [nosZF (CGC TGT TCI TCG ACA GYC AG)/nosZR (ATG TGC AKI GCR TGG CAG AA); [CITATION_2] ], and bacterial 16S rRNA genes [Eub341F (CCT ACG GGA GGC AGC AG)/Eub534R (ATT ACC GCG GCT GCT GG); [CITATION_3] from DNA samples were performed in three technical replicates per plot, sampling time point and soil depth as described [CITATION_4] . narG and nosZ amplified from cDNA obtained from the same fen samples during triplicate qPCRs yielded multiple bands on agarose gels and multiple melting points during melting curve analyses. Thus, narG and nosZ expression was not assessed. However, the bands with the correct size were excised from agarose gels and used for TRFLP analyses.",
